<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1088,1331]" box="[151,572,1088,1115]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1088,1115]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1088,1331]" box="[199,900,1124,1151]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1124,1151]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[454,553,1125,1151]" name="Portugal" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northernmost provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1088,1331]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1161,1187]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from four macrohabitat categories in 
<collectingCountry box="[850,948,1161,1187]" name="Portugal" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, most frequently from agricultural land. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sciapodinae" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[398,549,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Sciapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contristans">
<emphasis box="[398,549,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">S. contristans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most frequently found in dry open short-grazed biotopes (
<emphasis box="[1223,1256,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">e.g</emphasis>
., dry heathland, dunes) or open forests on sandy soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1088,1331]" box="[199,769,1268,1295]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1268,1295]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
12.6 (common). Fairly common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1088,1331]" box="[199,584,1304,1331]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1304,1331]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Activity period.</emphasis>
June–September.
</paragraph>
